  "prompt": "Why do I see the same questions in my Quora feed even if I refresh?",
  "response": "It's likely that Quora's algorithm is serving you questions that match your interests, which have been identified based on your previous activity on the site. Here are a few reasons why you might be seeing the same questions repeatedly:\n\n1. **Interest-Based Content:** Quora personalizes your feed based on topics you have shown interest in, such as questions you have followed, answered, or interacted with previously. This can lead to seeing similar questions multiple times.\n\n2. **Popular Questions:** Certain questions have higher engagement and popularity, making them more likely to appear in feeds frequently. If a question is currently trending or has a lot of activity, you might see it repeatedly.\n\n3. **Algorithm Limitations:** Quora's recommendation algorithm might have limitations or might overly rely on your past interactions, leading to the same questions being shown multiple times until new data updates your preferences.\n\n4. **Limited New Content:** If there is limited new content matching your interests, Quora may recycle existing content until fresh relevant questions are posted.\n\n5. **Question Following:** If you have followed a specific question, updates or new answers to that question might cause it to reappear in your feed.\n\n6. **Technical Issues:** Occasionally, there might be technical issues or glitches with the site that result in the same questions appearing repeatedly despite refreshing.\n\nIf you want more variety in your feed, you can try following different topics, engaging with various types of questions, or adjusting your settings to diversify your interests.",
